## Brief self-introduction [max 500 words]
I have lived and grown up in Taitung for 18 years, then moved to Hsinchu to study Power Mechanical Engineering in NTHU for bachelor's degree. After that, I applied for Electrical Control Engineering in NCTU for master's degree. Now under professor Jwu-Shen Hu's supervision. I love classical music and can play the cello and the piano. Also, I am a dedicated and persistant person who likes to try new things and devote as best as I can.

## Why Computer Vision? [max 500 words]
I have heard Computer Vision since I was a sophomore, but not until recent did I really know more about it. At first, I think Computer Vision is really cool, but after I took Image Processing course, I find Computer Vision, indeed, is really fascinating. I want to know more about how it works and this could greatly benefit my future experiments in my master's projects.

## What do you want to achieve in the course? [ max 500 words]
I want to expertise my ability on vision area, which includes fundamental knowledge, the developing platforms, future applications, and so on. Also, by utilizing these knowledge, I can attain higher achievements in my master's projects.

